            <bioghist>
                <p>John Goodrich was a Philadelphia merchant who did business at the southwest
                    corner of 3rd and Market Streets.</p>
            </bioghist>

            <scopecontent>
                <p>This is a ledger kept by John Goodrich between 1850 and 1853. The book is indexed
                    and lists charges to customers for goods such as flour, corn, coal, and lumber.
                    The volume also includes an itemized list of household items, with prices, “got
                    by M.C. Eck” in 1877.</p>
            </scopecontent>


